Package: faissR
Type: Package
Title: FAISS-Backed Nearest Neighbours, Graphs, kNN Models, and k-Means
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Stefano",
    family = "Cacciatore",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "tkcaccia@gmail.com")
Author: Stefano Cacciatore [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Stefano Cacciatore <tkcaccia@gmail.com>
Description: Native nearest-neighbour search, graph construction, k-nearest
    neighbour prediction, and k-means helpers for large dimensionality
    reduction workflows. The package requires the FAISS C++ library for CPU
    indexes and can optionally use FAISS GPU indexes with NVIDIA cuVS
    integration or direct RAPIDS cuVS/CUDA indexes on NVIDIA machines.
    CPU-only systems do not need NVIDIA libraries. Class probabilities are
    returned through predict(type = "prob") for kNN classification models.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/tkcaccia/faissR
BugReports: https://github.com/tkcaccia/faissR/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    methods,
    Rcpp
Suggests:
    igraph,
    Matrix,
    RcppHNSW,
    testthat
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
SystemRequirements: C++20, Fortran, FAISS C++ library, optional CUDA toolkit and RAPIDS cuVS library for CUDA/cuVS NN and k-means backends
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
Config/testthat/edition: 3
